## Step 2 вЂ” Build

`drydock build_plan <Project>` reads the specification and writes one plan file, `BUILD_PLAN.md`.
Dependencies are computed from the specification, so phases are never ordered by hand.

> Parallels Spec Kit `/plan` and `/tasks`. `/plan` computes the build order; `/tasks` is the
> resulting task list. In Drydock both are one operation вЂ” `build_plan` produces `BUILD_PLAN.md`,
> the computed task list, in a single step.

**`mode`** is the marker at the top of the file. It tells Run which kind of build to do:

```
# BUILD_PLAN: <Project>
mode: phased            # phased | agile
spec_commit: <hash>
```

### 2.1 Phased вЂ” known scope

The body is a list of `## Phase N` sections, each a group of specification files built together.

### 2.2 Agile вЂ” unknown scope

The body is a ticket board: features, stories, and spikes, each with acceptance criteria.
`drydock build_plan --agile` forces it.

The two file shapes are in **Appendix B**.

**TODO**
- One `BUILD_PLAN.md` with a `mode:` header, replacing today's two files (`build_plan.sh create`, `--analysis`)

## Step 3 вЂ” Run

`drydock run <Project> <Target>` executes `BUILD_PLAN.md` into software, creating the target
directory. Each step writes an **evidence** file; you review and sign off in the **Console**. The
sign-off writes your decision back to the plan. The Console is used in both modes.

Each step in the plan carries an `approval:` field вЂ” `auto` (default) or `manual` вЂ” that
determines whether `run` proceeds automatically or stops for human sign-off.

> Parallels Spec Kit `/implement` вЂ” executing the plan through an AI agent into working software.
> Where Spec Kit runs tasks sequentially with no phase awareness, Drydock rebuilds only the phases
> whose inputs changed and requires a human sign-off before continuing.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  classDef dir    fill:#0a5c38,stroke:#2cb67d,color:#fff,font-weight:bold
  classDef md     fill:#d4a017,stroke:#a07810,color:#111,font-weight:bold
  classDef script fill:#1e40af,stroke:#3b5fc0,color:#fff
  classDef output fill:#6d28d9,stroke:#8b5cf6,color:#fff,font-weight:bold
  BPF{{"BUILD_PLAN.md"}}:::md --> RUN[run]:::script
  RUN --> SW(["Working Software"]):::output
  RUN --> EV(["evidence/"]):::dir
  EV --> CON(["Console"]):::output
  SW --> CON
  CON --> SO[sign-off]:::script
  SO --> BPF
```

### 3.1 Phased run

Builds each phase as a separate AI session. The Dependency Staleness Check rebuilds only the phases
whose inputs changed вЂ” a content hash per input file, durable across a git clone where a
modification time is not.

### 3.2 Agile run

Builds one ticket at a time. After each story or spike, `run` checks the `approval:` field: if
`auto` and `bin/test.sh` exits 0, the step is approved and the build continues; if `manual`, the
build stops and waits for `drydock signoff`.

### 3.3 Sign-off

```
drydock signoff <Project> <Target> <StepId> approve|revise|reject [--feedback "<text>"]
drydock signoff <Project> <Target> <StepId> --set-approval auto|manual
```

| | |
|---|---|
| **`<Project>`** | Specification name |
| **`<Target>`** | Path to the built project directory вЂ” used to locate evidence files |
| **`<StepId>`** | `phase N` (phased) В· `spike N` В· `story N` (agile) |
| **`approve`** | Accept the step вЂ” build continues |
| **`revise`** | Return the step to the build agent with feedback; requires `--feedback` |
| **`reject`** | Permanently decline the step; build halts for that branch |
| **`--feedback`** | Revision note passed back to the build agent вЂ” required for `revise` and `reject` |
| **`--set-approval`** | Write `approval: auto\|manual` to the plan object вЂ” persists for future runs |

**Approval modes** (`approval:` field on each plan object):

| Mode | When to use | Auto-approval criteria |
|------|-------------|------------------------|
| `auto` | Default. Code generation, routine feature builds вЂ” passes if `bin/test.sh` exits 0. | Test suite green |
| `manual` | Architecture decisions, spike findings, any step where a human must read the evidence before the build continues. | None вЂ” always stops |

`approval:` is set per object in `BUILD_PLAN.md`. `build_plan` writes the default (`auto`);
override it with `--set-approval` or by editing the plan directly before running.

