## Step 4 вЂ” Iterate

`drydock iterate <Project> <Scope> "<Change>"` edits the specification and applies the change to code
in one pass. A downstream phase is dirtied only when a typed interface or a route changes.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  classDef dir    fill:#0a5c38,stroke:#2cb67d,color:#fff,font-weight:bold
  classDef script fill:#1e40af,stroke:#3b5fc0,color:#fff
  classDef prompt fill:#c2410c,stroke:#ea580c,color:#fff,font-weight:bold
  classDef output fill:#6d28d9,stroke:#8b5cf6,color:#fff,font-weight:bold
  SCOPE(["Scope В· URL В· keyword В· file"]):::dir --> IT["iterate В· SPEC | TGT | BOTH"]:::script
  SPEC(["Specification/"]):::dir --> IT
  IT --> P1(["edit spec"]):::prompt
  P1 --> P2(["apply to code"]):::prompt
  P2 --> PROJ(["Project"]):::output
```

## The engine

- **Rebuildable code** вЂ” nothing of value lives only in the output; the build is disposable.
- **One plan, one mode** вЂ” a single `BUILD_PLAN.md` serves both workflows.
- **Dependency Staleness Check** вЂ” content-hash provenance decides what to rebuild.
- **Syntax-aware injection** вЂ” agent rules are generated from `BUSINESS_RULES.md` and merged into
  every project between typed markers; a compact register shrinks the footprint per phase.

## Command summary

| Step | Spec Kit | Primitive | Today |
|------|----------|-----------|-------|
| **Setup** | `/constitution` В· `/specify` В· `/analyze` В· `/clarify` | `drydock new` В· `decompose` В· `analyze` В· `clarify` В· `validate` | `setup.sh` В· `decompose.sh` В· `setup.sh --analyze` В· `spec_iterate.sh` В· `validate.sh` |
| **Build** | `/plan` В· `/tasks` | `drydock build_plan [--agile]` | `build_plan.sh create` / `--analysis` |
| **Run** | `/implement` | `drydock run` В· `console` В· `signoff` | `oneshot_phased.sh` / `oneshot.sh` В· `Console/start.sh` В· `console_sync` В· `lib_agile_plan.py decide` |
| **Iterate** | `/specify` В· `/clarify` | `drydock iterate` В· `score` | `iterate.sh` В· `scorecard.sh` |

`drydock` is the target CLI вЂ” a thin dispatcher over the scripts in the **Today** column. It does not
exist yet; until it does, run the scripts directly.

## Appendix A вЂ” Drydock and the field

Three public tools share Drydock's thesis. GitHub Spec Kit's documentation is the clarity bar.

- **GitHub Spec Kit** вЂ” the interface standard: a `constitution.md` вЂ” a file of governing principles
  injected into every AI agent session, defining how the agent must behave and what conventions to
  follow. Nine articles; per-project. Drydock's equivalent is `BUSINESS_RULES.md`, generated into
  agent rules and injected syntax-aware between typed markers into every project. Command surface:
  `specify в†’ plan в†’ tasks в†’ implement`, across many agents.
- **Tessl** вЂ” specifications as a durable source of truth, with a registry of versioned specs.
  Drydock's regeneration and staleness check already deliver this.
- **AWS Kiro** вЂ” an agentic IDE: requirements with EARS acceptance criteria and steering files.

**Command mapping вЂ” Spec Kit to Drydock:**

| Spec Kit | Drydock | Step |
|----------|---------|------|
| `/constitution` | `INTENT.md` + stack files вЂ” governing intent and opinionated development guidelines | Setup 1.1вЂ“1.2 |
| `/specify` | Create `FEATURE-*.md`, `SCREEN-*.md`, `DATABASE.md` | Setup 1.3 |
| `/analyze` | `decompose.sh` (from code) В· `setup.sh --analyze` (from imported notes) | Setup 1.3.1вЂ“1.3.2 |
| `/clarify` | `spec_iterate.sh` вЂ” 7-dimension gap analysis, scored, tracked | Setup 1.3.3 |
| `/plan` | `build_plan.sh` вЂ” dependency graph в†’ phase order | Build |
| `/tasks` | `BUILD_PLAN.md` вЂ” the computed task list (output of `build_plan`) | Build |
| `/implement` | `drydock run` вЂ” rebuilds only stale phases; Console gate before continuing | Run |

**Capability comparison:**

| Concept | Spec Kit / Kiro | Drydock |
|---------|-----------------|---------|
| Governing rules | `constitution.md` / steering files | generated agent rules, injected everywhere |
| Specification | one `spec.md` | typed, decomposed files |
| Plan | `tasks.md`, hand-listed | one `BUILD_PLAN.md`, computed, phased or agile |
| Build | `/implement` | `drydock run` вЂ” rebuilds only stale phases |
| Review | none | the Console, with sign-off |
| Second build | none | `drydock iterate` вЂ” specification first |

## Appendix B вЂ” The BUILD_PLAN.md file

One file, two shapes. The `mode` field in the header selects which. `build_plan` writes it;
`run` reads the header and dispatches.

---

### B.1 Phased

The body is an ordered list of `## Phase` sections. Phase 1 is always the Foundation (database
and architecture); subsequent phases are feature/screen bundles ordered by the dependency graph.

**Header fields:**

| Field | Set by | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `# BUILD_PLAN: <Spec>` | `build_plan` | File title вЂ” the specification name |
| `mode: phased` | `build_plan` | Dispatch key вЂ” tells `run` to use the phased engine |
| `spec_commit:` | `build_plan` | Git SHA of the specification at plan time вЂ” used by the Dependency Staleness Check |

**Phase section fields:**

| Field | Set by | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `## <N>: <Name>` | `build_plan` | Phase number and human-readable name (e.g. `## 1: Foundation`) |
| `approval:` | `build_plan` / author | `auto` (default) В· `manual` вЂ” controls whether `run` auto-approves on green tests or stops for sign-off |
| `<SpecFile>.md` | `build_plan` | One spec file per line вЂ” the files built in this phase |
| `# stack: <list>` | `build_plan` | Optional вЂ” comma-separated stack file basenames for this phase, overriding auto-selection |

```
# BUILD_PLAN: MyApp
mode:        phased
spec_commit: a1b2c3d

## 1: Foundation
approval:    manual
DATABASE.md
ARCHITECTURE.md

## 2: Service Catalog
approval:    auto
FEATURE-CATALOG.md
SCREEN-CATALOG.md

## 3: Filing Importer
approval:    auto
FEATURE-IMPORTER.md
# stack: python, sqlite
```

At run time, `oneshot_phased.sh` reads each phase, resolves the stack files from the `Stack`
field in `INTENT.md` (auto-selecting compact variants for non-foundation phases), and checks the
Dependency Staleness Check вЂ” a content hash stored in `logs/oneshot_phase_N_meta.json` вЂ” to
determine whether the phase needs rebuilding.

---

### B.2 Agile

The body is a ticket board. Every object (spike, story, AC) carries its own `state:` field вЂ” the
plan IS the state; there is no JSON sidecar.

**Header fields:**

| Field | Set by | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `# BUILD_PLAN: <Spec>` | `build_plan` | File title |
| `mode: agile` | `build_plan` | Dispatch key вЂ” tells `run` to use the agile engine |
| `spec:` | `build_plan` | Specification name |
| `target:` | `run` | Absolute path to the target directory вЂ” written at run time |
| `plan_hash:` | `build_plan` | SHA-256 (first 12 chars) of the spec file at analysis time |
| `spec_commit:` | `build_plan` | Git SHA of the specification at analysis time |
| `updated:` | engine | ISO-8601 timestamp вЂ” updated by every state change |

**Spike fields** вЂ” a spike resolves an unknown before building:

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `## spike N: <name>` | Yes | Object header вЂ” the name is the spike topic |
| `summary:` | Yes | One-line synopsis for the board |
| `description:` | Yes | What the engineer must do вЂ” specific enough to act on |
| `question:` | Yes | The unknown this spike resolves |
| `approval:` | No | `manual` (default for spikes) В· `auto` вЂ” spikes default to manual; a human must read the finding |
| `inputs:` | No | Comma-separated spec files this spike reads |
| `evidence:` | No | Output file the spike writes вЂ” used to unblock dependent stories |
| `finding:` | No | One plain line вЂ” the result; empty until the spike runs |
| `state:` | Yes | `pending` В· `running` В· `awaiting_review` В· `approved` В· `revise` В· `rejected` |
| `decided_at:` | engine | ISO-8601 вЂ” set when the owner signs off |
| `feedback:` | engine | Owner's revision note вЂ” set on `revise` or `reject` |

**Story fields** вЂ” a story builds a deliverable:

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `## story N: <name>` | Yes | Object header |
| `summary:` | Yes | One-line synopsis for the board |
| `description:` | Yes | What to build вЂ” specific enough for an engineer to act on |
| `approval:` | No | `auto` (default for stories) В· `manual` вЂ” auto-approved when `bin/test.sh` exits 0 |
| `inputs:` | No | Comma-separated spec files and spike evidence files this story reads |
| `kind:` | No | `python` (default) В· `analysis` вЂ” the type of build session |
| `evidence:` | No | Output file the story writes |
| `finding:` | No | One plain line вЂ” the result; empty until run |
| `state:` | Yes | `pending` В· `running` В· `built` В· `tested` В· `accepted` В· `revise` В· `rejected` |
| `decided_at:` | engine | ISO-8601 вЂ” set when the owner signs off |
| `feedback:` | engine | Owner's revision note |

**AC (acceptance criterion) fields** вЂ” an AC is a testable assertion or guardrail on a parent:

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `## ac N: <criterion>` | Yes | Object header вЂ” the criterion text IS the name |
| `parent:` | Yes | `spike N` or `story N` вЂ” the object this AC tests |
| `origin:` | Yes | `dev` (team-defined) В· `po` (product-owner defect entered post-build) |
| `kind:` | Yes | `assertion` (positive вЂ” reconcile into spec when verified) В· `guardrail` (negative вЂ” permanent, never moved to spec) |
| `state:` | Yes | `open` В· `verified` В· `failed` |

```
# BUILD_PLAN: MyApp
mode:        agile
spec:        MyApp
target:
plan_hash:   a1b2c3d4e5f6
spec_commit: 4dca053
updated:     2026-06-07T12:00:00Z

## spike 1: PDF library selection
summary:     Identify the best PDF parsing library for the ingest pipeline.
description: Evaluate pdfplumber, pypdf2, and camelot against the sample filings.
question:    Which PDF library handles rotated tables reliably?
approval:    manual
inputs:      FEATURE-IMPORTER.md
evidence:    SPIKE_1_PDF_LIBRARY.md
finding:
state:       pending

## story 1: Filing importer
summary:     Ingest a filing and persist normalized rows.
description: Build the ingest endpoint, PDF parser, and database writer per FEATURE-IMPORTER.md.
approval:    auto
inputs:      FEATURE-IMPORTER.md, SPIKE_1_PDF_LIBRARY.md
kind:        python
evidence:    STORY_1_IMPORTER.md
finding:
state:       pending

## ac 1: importer rejects a duplicate filing
parent:    story 1
origin:    dev
kind:      assertion
state:     open

## ac 2: parser must not discard rotated tables
parent:    story 1
origin:    dev
kind:      guardrail
state:     open
```

